title: Saturday Mornings Greatest Hits
description:
This video is a truly altoonative collection of cartoon classics.  Hosted by Drew Barrymore this video features
footage from your favorite cartoons with unrestrained performances by some of today&#039;s hottest alternative acts.
Produced in 1995, with 60 minutes of run time.  Video featured groups and songs:

Matthew Sweet - Scooby-Doo, Where Are You?

Sublime - Hong Kong Phooey

Butthole Surfers - Underdog

Ramones - Spider-Man

Wax - Happy, Happy, Joy, Joy (from Ren and Stimpy)

Frente! - Let the Sun Shine In (from The Flintstones)

The Murmurs - H.R. Pufnstuf

face to face - I&#039;m Popeye the Sailoer Man

Collective Soul - The Bugaloos

Toadies - Goolie Get-Together (from The Groovie Goolies)

Mary Lou Lord - Sugar Sugar (from The Archies)

Tripping Daisy - Sigmund asd the Seamonsters

Sponge - Go Speed Racer Go

Helmet - Gigantor

Liz Phair - Banana Splits theme

Juliana Hatfield - Josie and the Pussycats

Reverend Horton Heat - Jonny Quest theme/Stop That Pigeon

Violent Femmes - Eep Opp Ork Ah-Ah (from The Jetsons)


Here&#039;s the story.  I am converting all of my old "fan Tapes" over from VHS to DVD and also ripping them to AVI files.
Hopefully I can post up some videos that are hard to find and help add to other peoples collections. There is a lot of 
of animation as well as some live action.  Sorry if the quality  is lacking on some of these old shows. Please try to 
remember that they are coming off of home recorded video tapes. Some of them are copies of copies and the tapes
have been in storage for a while. I have my system set for the best quality rip I can get, but I can only do so much.
Would love to hear feedback!

  SHARING IS CARING!  ..........oh yeah, PIRATE BAY IS THE BEST!
